                            <comment id="19548" author="green" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2011 21:38:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My digging around the dump seems to imply the crash actually happened in OBD_ALLOC somewhere., when we were trying to allocate md. Noy sure how did it die in the printing place then.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I think this is not exactly right in the patch:&lt;br/&gt;
const int instlen = sizeof(cfg-&amp;gt;cfg_instance) * 2 + 1;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should be +2, 1 for the dash between name and address and another 1 for the nul terminator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The previous code before the patch had the logic at +2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
